This paper involves machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and autoencoders to learn personalized optimal glycemic trajectories for septic patients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques for learning optimal policies, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves control engineering techniques for glycemic control, which suggests cs.CE (Control Engineering) as a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential impact on patient outcomes, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning for healthcare applications, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
